commit.message:
Put an #ifdef around the use of DB_DBT_READONLY,
for compatibility with older versions of bdb.

Provide our own version of the caml_alloc_initialized_string()
convenience function when compiling for versions of ocaml before 4.06.

Improve passing ocaml strings to bdb

Set DB_DBT_READONLY to indicate the string buffer is immutable
Explicitly cast away the "const" qualifier to avoid compiler warnings
Factor this out into a helper function
Use caml_alloc_initialized_string() to improve const-correctness (and concision).
add const qualifier to some constant variables
